                        </cit>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">καρπάσινος</foreign>) <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> linteum subtilissimum </quote>
                        </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> carbasinum </quote>
                        </cit>: Christus <foreign xml:lang="gez">በሰንዱነ፡ ገርዜን፡ ተቀብረ፡ በመቃብር፡</foreign> hom. Epiph. in <ref cRef="Cyr." loc="118">Cyr. f. 118</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">አምጽኡ፡ ልብሰ፡ ገርዜን፡ ለግንዘተ፡ ሥጋሁ፡</foreign> Lit. Chrys.; Christus <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘተጠብለለ፡ በልብሰ፡ ገርዜን፡</foreign> Org.; M.M. f. 3; <ref cRef="Sx. Hed." loc="29 ">Sx. Hed. 29 </ref>Enc.; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለምሥዋዕ፡ ይኩን፡ መንጦላዕት፡ ዘገርዜን፡ ንጹሕ፡ ዘአልቦ፡ ነውር፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Kid." loc="6">Kid. f. 6</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ክድንኒ፡ ገርዜነ፡ ጸጋ፡ ዘኢአነምዎ፡ ጠቢባን፡</foreign> <ref cRef="III Sal. Mar." loc="17.">III Sal. Mar. 17.</ref> – <lbl expand="Vocabularium Aethiopicum, -a -a">Voc. Ae.</lbl>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገርዜን፡ ዘ፡ ሻሽ፡</foreign>; <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
